Defendant Irene Nmi Taylor in court with attorney M E Weathers.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.     Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty. 

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

9 Months Huber (FIRST 60 days STRAIGHT TIME remaining time Huber (Credit - 4 days) HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.)

Term of Probation: 1 Year

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Be involved in 12 step program 2 times per week within 30 days and within 60 days have a sponsor;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Obtain a valid driver's license;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time activity;
- No contact with any BonTon Store and Boston Store in Southeastern Wisconsin.

Costs: $ 243.00  BAIL TO APPLY
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00  BAIL TO APPLY

Condition Time: 20 days Huber NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - Stayed and to be used at the agent's discretion.
